<p>Secret Service agents are at Mar-a-Lago to ensure physical security, not to run background checks on members, guests or workers for counterintelligence purposes. They are screened for weapons, but do not undergo the same rigorous vetting as visitors to the White House, where agents run every visitor&#8217;s full name, date and place of birth, Social Security number, city of residence, and more.</p>
